structured.description: An AuthenticationController class that implements the AuthenticationApi interface in a Spring Boot application. The class creates HTTP headers for logging in users and returns them in response entities using the AuthenticationService and LoginRequest objects.

items.description: Implements the AuthenticationApi interface and creates HTTP headers for logging in users based on provided authentication data. The class has one method, createLoginHeaders, which takes an AuthenticationData object as input and returns a set of HTTP headers containing the user ID and JWT token for authentication purposes.
items.name: AuthenticationController

items.description: Creates an HTTP headers object containing user ID and JWT token for authentication purposes.

params.name: authenticationData
params.description: user's login information, providing the user ID and JWT token required for authentication.

returns.description: a set of HTTP headers containing the user ID and JWT token for authentication purposes.

items.name: createLoginHeaders
